commit.message:
Broadcast vhost/base domains to front nodes via pm_registry

- pm_registry: get_static_domains/0 reads vhosts from app env;
  replay_to_nodes includes static domains alongside DETS entries;
  reload_static_domains/0 re-broadcasts current vhosts to all fronts;
  get_static_domains/0 exported for use by web handler;
  revoke/1 is unrestricted (no base-domain guard at registry level)
- personal_mtproxy_app: remove add/del_vhost_domains (direct
  mtp_policy_table calls); on_config_changed(vhosts) calls
  pm_registry:reload_static_domains(); stop/1 simplified
- pm_web_handler: DELETE /api/proxies returns 403 for base domains;
  shell admins can still force-remove via pm_registry:revoke/1
- README: document stale vhost caveat and shell escape hatch

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
